com.sap.conn.idoc.jco

Interface JCoIDocServer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JCoServer

    public interface JCoIDocServer
extends JCoServer
    JCoIDocServer is an extension of JCoServer and provides all additional abilities for IDoc related RFC server communication.

    Additional properties that can be specified by a ServerDataProvider:

    additional optional parameters
    idoc.jco.server.usePartnerProfileRelease    Flag indicating whether partner profiles should be queried if possible in order to create documents with the therein defined release; 1: on, 0: off (default).

      • setIDocRepository

        void setIDocRepository(JCoDestination destination)
        Sets the destination instance which is used for obtaining the default repository for querying IDoc metadata. A previously defined default repository that has been set by calling setIDocRepository(IDocRepository) will be overwritten by this method. If the property jco.server.repository_destination is configured for the server instance, it is not required to set the default repository instance with a separate API call.
        Parameters:
        destination - a destination being used for obtaining the default repository.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.11

      • setIDocRepository

        void setIDocRepository(IDocRepository repository)
        Sets the default repository instance which is being used for querying IDoc metadata. A previously defined repository destination that has been set by calling setIDocRepository(JCoDestination) will be overwritten by this method. If the property jco.server.repository_destination is configured for the server instance, it is not required to set the default repository instance with this API.
        Parameters:
        repository - an IDoc repository instance.

      • setIDocRepository

        void setIDocRepository(String sid,
                       String client,
                       JCoDestination destination)
                throws IDocRuntimeException
        Sets the repository destination instance for incoming IDoc RFC requests from the system with the system ID (SID) and - if defined - with the appropriate client. If the client is not relevant it may be null. If no matching SID and client combination is defined, the repository for the specified SID only will be used. If also no SID is defined, the current default repository will be used for processing the appropriate IDoc RFC request.
        An already defined corresponding repository rule that has been set before by calling setIDocRepository(String, String, IDocRepository) will be overwritten by this method.
        Parameters:
        sid - system ID of the SAP ABAP system containing exactly 3 characters.
        client - null or the client containing exactly 3 digits.
        destination - destination instance to be used for obtaining a repository if SID and client are matching.
        Throws:
        IDocRuntimeException - if sid or client are illegal.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.11

      • setIDocHandlerFactory

        void setIDocHandlerFactory(JCoIDocHandlerFactory idocHandlerFactory)
        Sets the JCoIDocHandlerFactory instance in order to be able to dispatch incoming RFC requests to the appropriate handler. The JCoIDocHandlerFactory instance should be set prior to calling method JCoIDocServer.start().
        Parameters:
        idocHandlerFactory - the IDoc handler factory to be used for incoming RFC requests.
